A vintage-style illustration of thousands of paper envelopes and letters swirling in a massive spiral vortex, being funneled down into an ornate brass mechanical contraption with gears, cogs, and pneumatic tubes. The machine sits on a wooden desk with an amber-glowing vacuum tube computer terminal beside it. The color palette features sepia tones, aged paper yellows, and warm copper metallics. Steam wisps rise from the mechanical device as it processes the endless stream of correspondence. The scene is rendered in the style of a Victorian-era technical illustration with crosshatching and fine line work, evoking the feeling of transforming chaos into order through ingenious engineering.
